      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "STORMY DAY (8) turned in a plain run last time when eighth at this track over 530m behind Needs Space (30.98) in a Grade 5. Was a winner the start prior. Has good speed and will be prominent from out wide. Has ability and is a key runner. RED EMPEROR (1) is going well, finishing in the placings twice in a row. Not beaten far last time when a half a length second (19.63) in a Grade 5 at this track. Has good early burn and is suited drawn on the inside. Key player on best and worth another try. TENACIOUS DESIGN (5) jumped cleanly and went straight to the lead, holding on for a place when third (19.67) at this track in a Grade 5 over 342m. Has good early speed so he should be prominent despite the squeeze draw. Winning chance. ALLINGA MERCURY (2) is another with top-three prospects.",
